.TH ZYGOLOPHODON 1 2025-02-01 "zygolophodon {{VERSION}}"
.SH NAME
zygolophodon \- CLI for reading Mastodon posts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY zygolophodon
.RB [ \-\-limit " \fIN\fP]"
.RB [ \-\-with\-ancestors ]
.I ADDRESS
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Zygolophodon
is an anonymous command-line interface
for reading microblogging posts,
chiefly for Mastodon.
.SS Supported servers
.IP \(bu 2
Mastodon (\(>= 3.4)
.IP \(bu 2
Iceshrimp, Catodon
.IP \(bu 2
Pleroma, Akkoma
.SS Supported addresses
The following address schemes are supported:
{{ADDRESS-LIST}}
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-\-limit " N
Request at most
.I N
posts.
The default is 40.
.TP
.B \-\-with\-ancestors
Show also ancestors of the post.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version information and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PAGER
If stdout is a terminal, zygolophodon pipes the output through
.BR $PAGER .
The default is
.B pager
(if it exists)
or
.BR more .
Setting
.B PAGER
to the empty string
or the value
.B cat
disables the use of the pager.
.\" TODO: ZYGOLOPHODON_COLUMNS
.\" TODO: ZYGOLOPHODON_LINK_SYMBOL
.\" TODO: ZYGOLOPHODON_PAPERCLIP
.TP
.B LESS
If this variable is unset,
zygolophodon sets it to
.B \-FXK
(which is equivalent to
.BR "\-\-quit\-if\-one\-screen \-\-no\-init \-\-quit\-on\-intr" ).
.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
{{EXAMPLE}}
.EE
